President Donald J. Trump has announced his intention to nominate Scott Stump of Colorado as Assistant Secretary for Career, Technical, and Adult Education at the Department of Education. Stump is currently the Chief Operating Officer for Vivayic, Inc., a learning solutions company, and has previously served as Assistant Provost for Career and Technical Education with the Colorado Community College System. He has also served as President of the National Association of State Directors of Career Technical Education consortium. Stump holds a B.S. in Agricultural Education from Purdue University.

Trump also intends to nominate Gordon Hartogensis of Connecticut as Director of the Pension Benefit Guaranty Corporation at the Department of Labor. Hartogensis is an investor and technology sector leader with experience in managing financial equities, bonds, private placements, and software development. He holds a B.S. in Computer Science from Stanford University and an M.S. in Technology Management from Columbia University.